                     <interp inst="t18320405-58-person605" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Sherman, a pawnbroker, of Sloane-street, Chelsea. On the 9th of March the prisoner pawned this sheet.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-58-person606">
                  RANDAL 
                  McDONALD
               <interp inst="t18320405-58-person606" type="surname" value="McDONALD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-58-person606" type="given" value="RANDAL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-58-person606" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I received the prisoner in charge; she said she had left the spoon at Mrs. Conden's, George-street, Richmond, but I could find no such person; the duplicate was found on her before I came.(Sheet produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never saw the spoon - I pawned the sheet for victuals.</p>
